// The peacetime job board, authored in the AMD quest vocabulary. Granted PER PLAYER SHIP
// by peacetime_remastered.mast (quest_grant_amd(p.id, ...)) so credit rewards pay to the
// side. The signals come from the mission's imperative plumbing (which stays in MAST):
//   drone_down / rock_cleared / poacher_killed  <- //damage/destroy routes
//   poacher_boarded / customs_cleared           <- poacher & customs comms
//   mercy_reached                               <- pr_mercy_watch proximity task
// Anomaly Survey uses the DECLARATIVE scan path: Goal: scan anomaly + Reveals: (the quest
// driver makes the anomalies scannable and renders the scan text - no //science route).
// The counts here are the target counts; pr_jobs_setup spawns matching objects - keep in sync.

# [Gunnery Qualification](job_gunnery)
---
State: active
Goal: signal 5 drone_down
Pays: 200 credits
---
Weapons drill: destroy all 5 target drones.

# [Rock Breakers](job_rocks)
---
State: active
Goal: signal 4 rock_cleared
Pays: 150 credits
---
Clear 4 hazard asteroids from the shipping lane.

# [Board the Poacher](job_poacher)
---
State: active
Goal: signal poacher_boarded
Fail on signal: poacher_killed
Pays: 300 credits
---
Disable the unregistered trawler (drop its shields below 50%) and demand its surrender. Do NOT destroy it.

# [Mercy Run](job_mercy)
---
State: active
Goal: signal mercy_reached
Fail after: 6 minutes
Pays: 250 credits
---
A shuttle is adrift and losing life support. Reach it before the clock runs out.

# [Customs Patrol](job_customs)
---
State: active
Goal: signal 4 customs_cleared
Pays: 120 credits
---
Hail and clear 4 civilian traders for transit.

# [Anomaly Survey](job_survey)
---
State: active
Goal: scan 3 anomaly
Reveals: Survey logged: a stable subspace distortion. No threat - filed with the science log.
Pays: 130 credits
---
Have Science scan 3 sensor anomalies and log them.
